# Axiom — Textbook-Scale Indexing Improvements

You are making targeted improvements to the Axiom indexing pipeline to handle large textbooks (500–1000+ pages) without blocking the app or making users think it has crashed.

The project is an Electron + TypeScript desktop app using `pdfjs-dist` for PDF extraction in a worker thread, `better-sqlite3` for metadata and FTS5, LanceDB for vector storage, and `chokidar` for file watching. The pipeline already streams chunks into SQLite and LanceDB during indexing — do not change this.

Read every section before writing any code. Implement strictly in the order listed.

---

## CRITICAL RULES — Read Before Touching Anything

Only make minimal targeted changes. Never refactor unrelated code. Never rewrite a function when a small edit will do.

Do NOT modify any of the following under any circumstances:

- `indexFile` per-file locking logic
- `purgeFile` logic
- Embedding pipeline, embed cache, or dual-worker architecture
- `EMBED_SUB_BATCH = 32` and `MAX_CHUNKS_PER_FILE = 5000` constants
- `MODEL_BATCH = 48`
- Chokidar watcher configuration including `awaitWriteFinish` and debounce
- SQLite schema or LanceDB schema
- Per-page extraction timeout (2000ms) and overall file timeout (120000ms)
- Minimum page word count check (20 words)
- Image-only PDF detection probe logic
- The `vault:indexProgress` IPC channel name
- Existing fields on the progress payload (`chunksProcessed`, `totalChunks`, `fileId`, `timestamp`) — only add new fields, never remove or rename existing ones

